cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SY, cs.CE 

The paper discusses the migration patterns of researchers in computer science, which falls under the broad category of sociology of computer science. The use of GeoDBLP to compile data on researcher migration suggests a focus on social informatics (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.SD). The statistical modeling of migration patterns also suggests a focus on cybernetics (cs.CY) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the implications for education and research worldwide suggest a focus on computer engineering (cs.CE).
